00:42:22.300 --> 00:42:27.020
to do that. Well, I mean, really, like what we've kind of gone, I've seen, you know, I have kids,

00:42:27.020 --> 00:42:33.020
and I've seen them learn coding with various, the various like self paced online things.

00:42:33.020 --> 00:42:39.260
One complaint I have would be, you you can learn some tricks, and you can learn, you know how to

00:42:39.260 --> 00:42:43.979
write a loop how to set a variable how to, you know, but you don't actually learn how to do the

00:42:43.979 --> 00:42:48.139
work. Because when you really sit down and do the work, you're really frustrated, you don't know

00:42:48.699 --> 00:42:52.780
how things you have to learn how to do research, you have to learn how to read error messages,

00:42:52.780 --> 00:42:58.540
there's like all this stuff that is not covered in these sort of, like, drilling on these tactical

00:42:58.540 --> 00:43:03.179
skills. So like what, like in with RStudio Academy, we've kind of gone the other way. It's

00:43:03.179 --> 00:43:07.739
like, let's, how can we have like a really thorough experience where people are doing real

00:43:07.739 --> 00:43:13.340
projects, and they have mentors, and it's like real work. So like, that's the kind of thing I'd

00:43:13.580 --> 00:43:18.620
So, like, that's the kind of thing I'd want to see in high school for high schoolers, like,

00:43:18.620 --> 00:43:21.820
you're actually doing real work, you have a mentor, not you're just like,

00:43:21.820 --> 00:43:29.979
you know, like cargo culting some tutorials. So, and that's the easy, like, it's easy to do the

00:43:29.979 --> 00:43:35.739
like, hey, look, self paced tutorial learning, you know, but it doesn't actually really, really

00:43:35.739 --> 00:43:41.100
get people where they need to be. So maybe some of the work that we're doing in Academy can

00:43:41.100 --> 00:43:46.939
eventually turn into like, hey, if you're if you want to teach a course in high school on data

00:43:46.939 --> 00:43:52.060
science, here's materials, and here's an approach. And here's like, here's a training thing you can

00:43:52.060 --> 00:43:55.979
go to. So maybe some of that will will lead lead in that direction.

