00:59:35.820 --> 00:59:38.219
benefit corp structure?

00:59:38.219 --> 00:59:43.419
I mean, the biggest thing that the biggest differentiating characteristic of public

00:59:43.419 --> 00:59:49.899
benefit corporations is that they are, unlike traditional C Corps, which the kind of the

00:59:51.020 --> 00:59:56.620
evolution of C Corps in the United States and the case law and things have made C Corps like

00:59:56.620 --> 01:00:00.939
really pretty much, they're pretty much exclusively beholden to their shareholders

01:00:00.939 --> 01:00:05.580
as the stakeholder that matters. The biggest thing about B Corps is it changes the

01:00:06.939 --> 01:00:13.820
corporate law and corporate charter so that your stakeholders are considered more broadly,

01:00:13.820 --> 01:00:19.659
your customers, your employees, your community, the environment, your shareholders, all

01:00:19.659 --> 01:00:26.219
stakeholders, and your duty is to run the company for the benefit of all stakeholders and to balance

01:00:26.860 --> 01:00:33.500
their concerns and interests. So that's the main thing. And then we also, the way the law

01:00:33.500 --> 01:00:39.419
works is you also establish a public benefit that you're accountable to working towards. In our

01:00:39.419 --> 01:00:48.620
case, it's open source software. We have, we actually get rated by the B Lab every three years.

01:00:49.659 --> 01:00:53.820
